# TechBridge Feature Expansion — 6-Phase Implementation Plan

Detailed build plan for expanding the TechBridge website across 6 phases, each completable in one focused session and safe to deploy independently.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **No coding until this plan is approved.** Each phase will be submitted for review before work begins on the next.

---

## Phase 1 — Homepage Quick Wins

**Goal:** Improve the homepage with quick wins that don't require new routes.  
**Estimated complexity:** Moderate — 5 independent changes touching 4 existing files + 1 new file.

### Proposed Changes

---

#### Homepage Components

##### [NEW] `src/components/home/TrustedBy.tsx`
- New section placed directly below `<Hero />` in the homepage composition.
- Displays a "Trusted By" client logo bar for NextLex, PrimeMark Apparel, and AliWali Trading Co.
- Uses **text-based logo placeholders** styled with `font-mono font-bold text-white tracking-widest uppercase` inside a glass-card border treatment (`border border-white/8 bg-white/[0.03] rounded-xl`). No SVG logos exist in the project.
- Follows the section wrapper pattern (`relative overflow-hidden py-20 lg:py-28` — lighter padding since this is a slim trust bar, not a content section).
- Uses a simple [fadeUp](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/websites/page.tsx#13-22) animation triggered by `useInView({ once: true })`.
- Eyebrow text: none (this section is intentionally minimal — just logos with a subtle leading text like "Trusted by teams at" in `text-xs text-zinc-600`).

##### [MODIFY] [src/components/home/Hero.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/Hero.tsx)
- Upgrade the `STATS` bar (`50+`, `98%`, `3×`) with **count-up animations**.
- Implementation: Extract a `CountUp` helper component that uses `useMotionValue` + `animate()` from Framer Motion (not a third-party library).
- On `useInView` trigger, animate each `MotionValue` from `0` to the target number over ~1.5s with the global `EASE` curve.
- Parse the stat value to extract the numeric part and suffix (e.g., `"50+"` → animate `0 → 50`, then append `"+"`; `"98%"` → animate `0 → 98`, then append `"%"`; `"3×"` → animate `0 → 3`, then append `"×"`).
- Use `useTransform` to round the animated value to an integer for display.

##### [MODIFY] [src/components/home/TechStackMarquee.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/TechStackMarquee.tsx)
- Add hover tooltips to each [TechCard](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/TechStackMarquee.tsx#109-129) component.
- Add a `tooltip` field to the [TechItem](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/TechStackMarquee.tsx#10-15) interface and populate the `STACK` data array with 1-line descriptions (e.g., `"Next.js — Server-first React framework for SEO and performance"`).
- On hover, show a small tooltip div positioned absolutely above the card: `absolute bottom-full left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 mb-2 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-neutral-900/90 backdrop-blur-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-xs text-zinc-300 whitespace-nowrap`.
- Use `AnimatePresence` + `motion.div` for a smooth fade-in/out (`opacity: 0 → 1`, `y: 4 → 0`, duration: 0.2s).
- Managed via local `useState<string | null>` on each [TechCard](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/TechStackMarquee.tsx#109-129) (no global state needed).

##### [MODIFY] [src/components/home/CaseStudies.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/CaseStudies.tsx)
- Convert to a **teaser style**: show only client name, one key metric, and one sentence (truncate `description` to first sentence or max 80 chars).
- Remove the scroll-pinned [PinnedCaseStudy](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/CaseStudies.tsx#55-161) component and the Remotion `CaseStudyReel` player integration. Replace with a simpler horizontal card layout or tight grid.
- Add a prominent "See All Work →" link at the bottom, using the existing text-link CTA pattern, linking to `/work`.
- Remove `@remotion/player` import from this file (the full experience lives on `/work` now).

> [!NOTE]
> The full case study experience (scroll-scrubbed Remotion players) will still live on `/work`. This change reduces homepage weight and eliminates content duplication.

##### [MODIFY] [src/components/layout/Navbar.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/layout/Navbar.tsx)
- Add an **8-second auto-dismiss timer** to the announcement banner.
- Implementation: Add a `useEffect` that starts a `setTimeout(8000)` calling `setBannerVisible(false)` when the banner is visible. Clear the timeout on manual dismiss or unmount.
- The existing `AnimatePresence` + `exit` animation (`height: 0, opacity: 0`) already provides the smooth fade-out — no additional animation work needed.

##### [MODIFY] [src/app/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/page.tsx)
- Import and insert `<TrustedBy />` between `<Hero />` and `<Services />`.
- Updated section order: `Hero → TrustedBy → Services → HowItWorks → WhyChooseUs → TechStackMarquee → CaseStudies → CTA`.

### Work Order
1. `TrustedBy.tsx` (new, self-contained)
2. [Hero.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/Hero.tsx) count-up (isolated to STATS rendering)
3. [TechStackMarquee.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/TechStackMarquee.tsx) tooltips (isolated to TechCard)
4. [CaseStudies.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/CaseStudies.tsx) teaser conversion (most complex — structural change)
5. [Navbar.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/layout/Navbar.tsx) auto-dismiss timer (simple timer addition)
6. [page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/page.tsx) import insertion (trivial, last step)

### Decisions Needed
1. **CaseStudies layout:** Should the teaser cards be a **3-column grid** (compact) or a **horizontal scroll row** (more visual)? I recommend 3-column grid on desktop, stacked on mobile.
2. **TrustedBy position:** Confirmed directly below Hero? Or would you prefer it at the very bottom above CTA as a "credibility close"?

---

## Phase 2 — Testimonials & Social Proof

**Goal:** Add a new testimonial carousel section to the homepage.  
**Estimated complexity:** Moderate — 1 new file + 1 modified file.

### Proposed Changes

---

#### Homepage Components

##### [NEW] `src/components/home/Testimonials.tsx`
- New section component following the standard section wrapper pattern.
- **Section header:** Eyebrow "Client Voices" → H2 "What Our Partners Say." → No subtitle.
- **Design:** Carousel/slider showing 1 testimonial card at a time (3 total), with horizontal slide transitions.
- **Card structure** (glass card pattern):
  - Large opening quote mark (`"`) as a decorative element in `text-6xl text-violet-500/20 font-serif`.
  - Quote text: `text-base lg:text-lg leading-relaxed text-zinc-300 italic` (2-3 sentences).
  - Client info block: Name (`text-sm font-semibold text-white`), Title + Company (`text-xs text-zinc-500`).
  - Optional avatar: styled `div` with initials (`h-10 w-10 rounded-full bg-violet-950/60 border border-violet-500/20 flex items-center justify-center font-mono text-xs text-violet-300`).
- **Data:** `TESTIMONIALS` const array at module scope, 3 placeholder entries. Easy to swap — just edit the array.
- **Auto-advance:** `useEffect` with `setInterval(6000)` cycling `activeIndex`. Resets interval on manual navigation.
- **Navigation:** Dot indicators below the card (`h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full` — `bg-violet-400` active, `bg-zinc-700` inactive), clickable.
- **Animation:** `AnimatePresence` with horizontal slide transition (`x: 60 → 0 → -60`), duration 0.5s with `EASE`.

##### [MODIFY] [src/app/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/page.tsx)
- Import `Testimonials` and insert between `<CaseStudies />` and `<CTA />`.
- Updated order: `Hero → TrustedBy → Services → HowItWorks → WhyChooseUs → TechStackMarquee → CaseStudies → Testimonials → CTA`.

### Work Order
1. `Testimonials.tsx` (self-contained build + test)
2. [page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/page.tsx) insertion

### Decisions Needed
1. **Carousel vs stacked cards:** I recommend a carousel (1 visible at a time) for testimonials since quotes are personal and benefit from focused reading. Alternatively, show all 3 in a grid. Preference?

---

## Phase 3 — Detailed Case Study Pages

**Goal:** Create dynamic case study detail pages with individual routes.  
**Estimated complexity:** Complex — 2 new files + 1 new data file + 3 existing files modified.

### Proposed Changes

---

#### Case Study Data & Routing

##### [NEW] `src/data/case-studies.ts`
- Centralized case study data file. Exports a `CASE_STUDIES` typed array and a `getCaseStudy(slug: string)` helper function.
- Each entry contains: `slug`, `client`, `sector`, `metric`, `metricLabel`, `heroDescription` (1-liner), `problem` (2-3 paragraphs placeholder), `solution` (2-3 paragraphs placeholder), `results` (array of `{ stat, label }` objects for count-up), `techStack` (string array), `tags` (string array), `assets` (image paths from `/proofs/`), `liveUrl`, `accentColor`.
- **Existing 3 entries:** `nextlex`, `primemark`, `aliwali`.
- **2 new placeholder entries:** e.g., `internal-ops-dashboard` (internal tool project), `saas-analytics-platform` (SaaS project). These get placeholder content to flesh out the portfolio. Assets can reuse generic screenshots or use styled placeholder divs.

##### [NEW] `src/app/work/[slug]/page.tsx`
- Server Component with `generateStaticParams()` returning all slugs from the data file.
- Imports the data and renders client sub-components.
- **Page structure (6 sections):**
  1. **Hero:** Project name (h1), key metric (large `font-mono`), industry tag pill, 1-line description, gradient accent based on `accentColor`.
  2. **Problem:** Eyebrow "The Challenge" → 2-3 paragraph block with left-aligned content.
  3. **Solution:** Eyebrow "Our Approach" → 2-3 paragraph block. Optionally include a tech decision callout card (glass card with icon).
  4. **Results:** Eyebrow "The Impact" → Grid of 3-4 metric cards with count-up animation (reuse the `CountUp` component from Phase 1's [Hero.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/Hero.tsx)— extract it to `src/components/shared/CountUp.tsx` for reuse).
  5. **Tech Stack:** Simple tag pill list of technologies used.
  6. **Screenshots:** Image gallery using `public/proofs/[Project]/` images. Grid layout with `rounded-2xl border border-white/8 overflow-hidden`. Clicking opens a lightbox-style modal.
  7. **CTA:** Section with "Ready to build something like this?" heading + "Book a Discovery Call" primary CTA + "View Live Site ↗" secondary link to `liveUrl`.
- Each section uses the standard section wrapper, header, and fadeUp animation patterns.
- Per-page SEO metadata via `generateMetadata()`: `"[Client] Case Study | [Sector] — TechBridge"`.

##### [NEW] `src/components/shared/CountUp.tsx`
- Extract the count-up animation logic from Phase 1's Hero.tsx modification into a reusable component.
- Props: `value: number`, `suffix?: string`, `prefix?: string`, `duration?: number`, `className?: string`.
- Used by: Hero stats bar, case study results sections.

##### [MODIFY] [src/components/home/CaseStudies.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/CaseStudies.tsx)
- Update teaser cards to link to `/work/[slug]` instead of external `liveUrl`.
- Each card uses `<Link href={'/work/${study.slug}'}'>` as the primary action.

##### [MODIFY] [src/app/work/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/work/page.tsx)
- Import case study data from `src/data/case-studies.ts` instead of the inline `PROJECTS` array.
- Update card links: primary click → `/work/[slug]`, secondary "View Live Site ↗" link kept for external URL.
- Add the 2 new placeholder entries to the rendered list, styled identically to existing cards.
- Ensure the parallax SVG patterns rotate through for new entries (existing pattern system handles this).

##### [MODIFY] [src/app/websites/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/websites/page.tsx)
- Update `SOCIAL_PROOF_PROJECTS` data to reference centralized `src/data/case-studies.ts` where overlapping (NextLex, PrimeMark, AliWali). Or keep separate since the 24-Hr Studio page has its own presentation context — this is a judgment call.

### Work Order
1. `src/data/case-studies.ts` (data foundation — everything depends on this)
2. `src/components/shared/CountUp.tsx` (extract from Hero.tsx Phase 1 work)
3. `src/app/work/[slug]/page.tsx` (new route, biggest piece)
4. [src/components/home/CaseStudies.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/CaseStudies.tsx) (link updates)
5. [src/app/work/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/work/page.tsx) (data source swap + new entries)
6. [src/app/websites/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/websites/page.tsx) (optional data alignment)

### Decisions Needed
1. **Shared data vs duplicate:** Should [websites/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/websites/page.tsx) import from the centralized data file, or keep its own `SOCIAL_PROOF_PROJECTS` array? The websites page has different fields (`metrics`, `metricSubtitle`, Remotion player config). I recommend **keeping separate** with a comment referencing the shared source.
2. **Screenshot gallery interaction:** Simple grid, or lightbox modal on click? I recommend lightbox for premium feel.
3. **Placeholder project names:** Are `Internal Ops Dashboard` and `SaaS Analytics Platform` acceptable placeholder names, or do you have real projects to use?

