## Phase 4 — About Page Overhaul

**Goal:** Restructure the About page with new sections for depth and credibility.  
**Estimated complexity:** Complex — 1 major file rewrite, potentially extracting sections into sub-components.

### Proposed Changes

---

#### About Page

##### [MODIFY] [src/app/about/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/about/page.tsx) (major rewrite)

Keep the existing hero heading ("Engineering as a discipline. Not an afterthought.") but restructure everything below it into 7 sections:

**Section 1 — Founder Story** (Eyebrow: "The Founder")
- Name placeholder, headshot placeholder (styled `div` with initials: `h-24 w-24 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-950 to-indigo-950 border border-violet-500/20 flex items-center justify-center font-mono text-2xl text-violet-300`).
- 2-paragraph founder bio following content-guide.md voice: personal, principled, using "we believe" and first-person.
- Layout: 2-column — image left, text right (stacked on mobile).

**Section 2 — Team** (Eyebrow: "The Engineering Team")
- 3 team member cards (2 engineering, 1 design/ops placeholder).
- Each card: headshot placeholder (initials div), name, role, 2-line bio.
- Lahore engineering team framed as **core engineering team**, not outsourced — language like "Our Lahore studio leads the engineering on every build" per the content guide's tone.
- Glass card pattern with stagger animation.

**Section 3 — Company Timeline** (Eyebrow: "Our Journey")
- Vertical timeline with **5 milestone entries** (founding, first client, first SaaS launch, Lahore office established, 50th project shipped).
- Reuse the timeline/vertical-rail pattern from [HowItWorks.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/components/home/HowItWorks.tsx) and [websites/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/websites/page.tsx) Timeline component: dot rail + glass cards with scroll-linked glow line.
- Placeholder dates that are easy to swap.

**Section 4 — Core Values** (Eyebrow: "What We Stand For")
- Differentiated from homepage "TechBridge Advantage" by going deeper: each value gets a short **story or example** (2-3 sentences), not just a bullet point.
- 3-4 values max. Layout: single column, full-width cards with quote-style callouts.
- Different values than the homepage (e.g., "Transparency in Timelines", "Code That Outlives Us", "Direct Communication") to avoid repetition.

**Section 5 — How We're Different** (Eyebrow: "The Comparison")
- Comparison table identical in structure to the one on `/websites` ([ComparisonTable](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/websites/page.tsx#197-260) component).
- Columns: `Typical Agency` | `Freelancer` | `TechBridge`.
- Rows: Team composition, Code ownership, Timeline accuracy, Post-launch support, Tech stack modernity, Communication model.

**Section 6 — Security & Compliance** (Eyebrow: "Trust & Security")
- Small block (not a full section — more of a feature strip).
- 4 items in a horizontal grid: GDPR Awareness, Secure Coding Practices, Encrypted Communications, SOC 2 Readiness.
- Each item: icon (from Lucide: `Shield`, `Lock`, `ShieldCheck`, `FileCheck`) + title + 1-line description.
- Glass card pattern, compact sizing.

**Section 7 — CTA** (Eyebrow: "Start a Conversation")
- Reuse the CTA pattern from the homepage CTA.tsx.
- Heading: "Ready to meet the team behind the code?" with "meet the team" in gradient.
- Primary CTA: "Book a Discovery Call" → `/contact`.
- Secondary CTA: "View Our Work" → `/work`.

### Work Order
1. Plan the section component breakdown — decide if sections should be extracted into `src/components/about/` sub-files or kept inline (recommendation: **keep inline** since this is one page and the file will be ~500-600 LOC, similar to existing [services/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/services/page.tsx) and [work/page.tsx](file:///f:/Techbridge/premium-next-app/src/app/work/page.tsx)).
2. Rewrite from top to bottom, section by section.
3. Test each section's responsive layout and animations.

### Decisions Needed
1. **Founder name:** Should I use a placeholder like "Sajawal Ali Sohail" or a generic "Founder Name"? I'll use a placeholder that's easy to find-and-replace.
2. **Team member count:** The plan has 3. Want more?
3. **Core Values:** The plan differentiates from homepage by using different values and adding stories. Do you want to keep any of the 4 existing values (AI-Native Engineering, Zero Bloat, Rapid Execution, Enterprise-Grade Foundations), or completely fresh ones?

