| `/work` | `"Work \| Case Studies & Portfolio — TechBridge"` | `"See how we've helped businesses..."` |
| `/websites` | `"24-Hour Websites \| Premium Web Presence — TechBridge"` | `"Launch a custom-coded website..."` |
| `/blog` | `"Insights \| Engineering Blog — TechBridge"` | `"Thinking from the TechBridge..."` |
| `/privacy` | `"Privacy Policy — TechBridge"` | `"Our privacy practices and data..."` |
| `/terms` | `"Terms of Service — TechBridge"` | `"Terms governing use of TechBridge..."` |

> [!NOTE]
> The `/work/[slug]` and `/blog/[slug]` pages already get per-page metadata via `generateMetadata()` in Phases 3 and 5.

### Work Order
1. SEO metadata (layout.tsx + all page files — quick systematic pass)
2. Services page reframe (quote rename + icon area)
3. Contact page Cal.com embed (new section)
4. Work page card sizing (CSS adjustments)
5. Websites page tags + placeholder entries
6. Footer links + clock verification
7. Privacy + Terms placeholder pages

### Decisions Needed
1. **Cal.com URL:** Is `https://cal.com/techbridge` the correct placeholder, or do you have a real Cal.com link to use?
2. **Metadata template:** Should the root layout use Next.js `title.template` (e.g., `"%s — TechBridge"`) so child pages only set `title: "About"` and it auto-appends? I recommend yes.

---

## Verification Plan

Since the project has no existing test infrastructure (no test files in `src/`), verification will be visual + build-based.

### Automated Verification (every phase)
```bash
# 1. TypeScript compilation check
npm run build

# 2. Linting
npm run lint

# 3. Dev server smoke test
npm run dev
# Verify no console errors on every affected route
```

### Visual Verification (browser-based, every phase)

After each phase, I will use the browser tool to:
1. Navigate to every affected route
2. Verify sections render correctly (layout, spacing, content)
3. Verify animations trigger on scroll
4. Check responsive layout at mobile viewport (375px width)
5. Verify no broken links or missing images
6. Capture screenshots for the walkthrough

### Phase-Specific Checks

| Phase | Routes to verify | Key checks |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `/` | TrustedBy visible below hero · Count-up animates on scroll · Tooltips show on marquee hover · CaseStudies is teaser-style · Banner auto-dismisses after 8s |
| 2 | `/` | Testimonials carousel auto-advances · Dots navigate · Animation smooth |
| 3 | `/`, `/work`, `/work/nextlex`, `/work/primemark`, `/work/aliwali` | Detail pages render · Links from homepage and /work go to detail pages · Count-up works on results · Image gallery renders |
| 4 | `/about` | All 7 sections render · Timeline scrolls correctly · Comparison table renders · CTA section present |
| 5 | `/blog`, `/blog/[slug]`, `/` | Listing page shows 4 posts · Detail page renders cleanly · Nav link works · Homepage shows 2 latest |
| 6 | All routes | Per-page titles verified · Cal.com iframe visible · Cards larger on /work · Footer links work · Privacy/Terms pages render |

### Manual Verification (user)
After all 6 phases are complete, the user should:
1. Review all pages in a browser at desktop and mobile widths
2. Verify placeholder text is easy to find and replace (search for `TODO` and `placeholder` comments)
3. Confirm the timezone clocks show correct local times
4. Replace the Cal.com iframe URL with the real scheduling link
